Finally, the game's title screen includes the following disclaimer:
{i}The story, all names, characters, and incidents portrayed in this production are fictitious. No identification with actual persons, places, buildings, and products is intended or should be inferred.{/i}
Well then...

Within a glass case sits a small, official-looking stamper with a laminated sign propped up next to it, featuring an arrow pointing to the aforementioned stamper along with a carefully calligraphed message reading:
{b}Eros District Stamp - For adventurers only! - 250 tickets!{/b}
You have [ProgressDisplay] Arcade tickets to spend.
